title.narrative: Support to Ethnic Tibetans in China

description.narrative: (China): The activity builds business skills, expands producers' technical capacity, and strengthens linkages across local, regional, and international markets for ethnic Tibetans in China. By focusing on complementary livelihood opportunities such as yak and sheep herding, marketing services, and handicrafts that can be pursued during slow times in the agricultural calendar, the activity aims to create synergies that will make a significant contribution to the income available to Tibetan communities. To achieve these results, the activity will develop community-specific livelihood strategies and improve Tibetan entrepreneurship and businesses. Improvements will be made through market-readiness training and business development workshops, market-driven production development and design innovation, and improved market development and buyer linkages. These activities help targeted businesses and entrepreneurs to create products that align with market demands and increase their customer bases in domestic and international markets..
